content: 10-Spot Constraint discovered: 'Only get 10 spots on college application.' Current 8 filled, 2 gaps. Jenny: 'No reason to over exert yourself for more than 10.' Quality over quantity. Strategic selection crucial. Stop activity accumulation.

Credibility Gap Diagnosis: 'Lacking credibility with larger orgs. All stuff self-initiated, which is impressive, but need basis to assess leadership ability.' Solution: attach to established organizations. Balance creation with collaboration. MYNA, Girls Make Games, government internship introduced.

Newly Declared City Opportunity: Mountain House no Instagram/Facebook. 'Volunteer to create social media presence. Big impact in newly declared city.' Pioneer infrastructure role. Quantifiable metrics. Resume: 'Social Media Manager for City.' First-mover advantage.

Priority Honesty Protocol: Folklift 'impact has been minimal,' Youth Action 'not really' interested. Jenny: 'It's okay, trying to get a sense.' Accepts when student admits low priority. Reallocates energy rather than forcing commitment. Not everything needs equal investment.

Age Limitation Workaround: Women Make Games requires 18+. Jenny: 'Apply for their camp instead, they do scholarships.' Every closed door has adjacent opening. Same organization, different entry point. Alternative pathways when primary blocked.

Summer Architecture Method: Complete mapping with intentional gaps. KWK June 17-28 → London July 1-10 → Empowering AI hackathon July 20-21 → JCamp Aug 3-9. Programs + vacation + self-initiated. Structured with buffers. Every week purposeful. No wasted time, no burnout.

Session outcomes: All A's celebrated, summer finalized (KWK/London/hackathon/JCamp), 10-spot strategy defined (8 filled, 2 targets), Cameron Impact urgent (5 days), MYNA discovered, Mountain House social media opportunity identified, credibility gap diagnosed, priority honesty established.

Multi-platform opportunity discovery: Tracy Press found through friend's article, MYNA through Jenny's Stanford friends, government internship researched during session, Mountain House gap identified real-time. Network leveraging plus active research creates opportunity flow.

Technical Grace: Camera only showing chair. 'No worries. Take your time.' Multiple fix attempts. 'Maybe we can just get started.' Cultural Understanding: MSA toxicity acknowledged. Alternative: 'Community branch without toxicity.' MYNA connections: 'Some of my friends at school involved.'

Local Journalism Hack: Find reporters through friends' coverage. Student saw friend's article → contacted author → pitched NCWIT story → Tracy Press interview secured. Multiplier: local coverage validates achievement. Accessible pathway to media visibility through existing relationships.
